What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Smart Water Monitoring Market?

Market Analysis and Insights:

Global Smart Water Monitoring Market

The smart water monitoring market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 12.4% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 29,744.19 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on smart water monitoring market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The rise in demand for quality water services globally is escalating the growth of smart water monitoring market.

Smart water monitoring refers to a solution that assists in monitoring of water quality and helps in providing safe water. These solutions are not only used to water utilities and large water plants but they are also being highly deployed at corporate and residential levels.

The increase in the need to replace aging water infrastructure across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of smart water monitoring market. The rise in demand for the solution because of the rising water concerns caused by pollution and uneven resources and increase in government initiatives and regulatory implementations for promoting smart water solutions accelerate the smart water monitoring market growth. The advent of integrated mobile technology assisting monitor pumps remotely to detect any malfunction or leakages efficiently and rising digitalization of the utility sector further influence the smart water monitoring market. Additionally, growth in population, rise in need for sustainable water solutions, research and development activities and surge in investment positively affect the smart water monitoring market. Furthermore, rising global smart city initiatives and technological advancements to offer features such as security, pressure control, and quality sensors extend profitable opportunities to the smart water monitoring market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high initial investments and lower return on investment and issues with the technology implementation over the legacy infrastructure are the factors expected to obstruct the smart water monitoring market growth. Decline in shelf life of smart meters and lack of digitally skilled workforce are projected to challenge the smart water monitoring market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

